cs.SC, cs.CG, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the formalisation of a proof in real algebraic geometry using algebraic tools. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper involves the use of circles and straight lines to delimit areas in the complex plane. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses the Coq proof assistant to formalise the proof. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses an algorithm for isolating real roots of a univariate polynomial. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves the use of geometric concepts such as circles and straight lines.
